# Lab 05: Implementing Secure Authentication with MFA, SSPR & Password Protection

## ğŸ” Overview

This lab demonstrates the implementation of **modern authentication and identity security controls** using **Microsoft Entra ID (Azure AD)**. The lab focuses on enforcing **tenant-wide Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA)**, configuring **authentication methods**, enabling **Self-Service Password Reset (SSPR)**, and implementing **Microsoft Entra Password Protection** in alignment with **Zero Trust principles**.

This lab reflects real-world Identity & Access Management (IAM) administrative tasks commonly performed by Identity Engineers and Security Administrators.

---

## ğŸ¯ Objectives

* Review and plan authentication methods in Microsoft Entra ID
* Configure and enforce tenant-wide MFA
* Enable and manage authentication methods (Authenticator, TAP, Email OTP)
* Deploy Self-Service Password Reset (SSPR)
* Implement Microsoft Entra Password Protection
* Validate security controls through user testing

---

## ğŸ› ï¸ Technologies Used

* Microsoft Entra ID (Azure Active Directory)
* Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA)
* Microsoft Authenticator
* Temporary Access Pass (TAP)
* Self-Service Password Reset (SSPR)
* Microsoft Entra Password Protection
* Zero Trust Identity Principles

---

## ğŸ“‹ Prerequisites

* Microsoft Entra ID tenant
* Global Administrator role
* Two test user accounts
* Microsoft Authenticator app installed on a mobile device

---

## ğŸ§ª Task 1: Review Authentication Methods

Reviewed available authentication options within Microsoft Entra ID, including Microsoft Authenticator, Temporary Access Pass (TAP), FIDO2 security keys, OATH tokens, and Email OTP.

